userdoc.notice: Simple bank contract where users can deposit, withdraw and check their balance. - Each Ethereum address has its own balance tracked in the contract. - Deposits can be made via `deposit()` or by sending ETH to the contract (receive/fallback). - Withdrawals send ETH back to the caller, with a safety check for sufficient balance.

documentation.text: Receive function: credits sender's balance when contract receives ETH with empty calldata.
Fallback function: credits sender if ETH is sent with non-empty calldata.
